H0.text: A marsupial is a therian mammal in which the embryo is born at an early, immature stage.

H1.text: Rodent is a therian mammal in which the embryo is born at an early, immature stage.

H2.text: Bat is a therian mammal in which the embryo is born at an early, immature stage.

H3.text: Carnivore is a therian mammal in which the embryo is born at an early, immature stage.

A4.text: The baby (joey) is born in a fetal state, equivalent to an 8–12 week human fetus, blind, furless, and small in comparison to placental newborns: sizes range from 4–800g+.

A5.text: Marsupials are altricial animals, needing intensive care following birth.
